abstract: IT takes about three-quarters of an hour to figure out where "Why Would I Lie?" is going, and by  that time it's clear the movie won't get there. As comedies go this one is odd, very odd. Its characters have funny names--Cletus, Jeorge and Mrs. Bok, to name just three.

abstract: NO human activity takes more different forms than eating-- from raiding the refrigerator to a ceremonial banquet. The  history of civilization can be charted by refinements in dining, and the history of taste can be recorded in objects for the table.
headline_main: Design Notebook; The art of dining has produced many beautiful objects.
